From now on, I am having Chat AI write my descriptions, so here is what it wrote about today 🤯
"Just experienced the ultimate Alaskan splitboarding adventure! Started off in a whiteout, but the weather cleared up just in time for us to shred down the mountain with blue skies above. The snow was absolutely perfect. This is why we live for days like this! #splitboarding #Alaska #blueskies #perfectsnow"

Hatcher Pass was all time today! Headed up at the crack of dawn with @ftrainer94 @travismcadamz @davidmcminn and got some of the best riding yet this year! It's pretty amazing living in Alaska and being able to get out on days like today. 
The only downside was forgetting my food in the car, so by the time I got back to the car, I was crazy dizzy 😵

Some drone footage of myself and @reece.boby from this week's hut trip here in AK. Unfortunately, the light was a bit flat most of the trip but still had a good time, and the snow for the most part was pretty good. Snowboard / splitboarding / skiing out here is pretty wild
#huttrip #manitoba #turnagainarm #dji #flylow #smithgoggles #splitboarding #snowboarding

Who says winter is dull? 😎 Today was all about splitboarding in the powder at Arctic Valley and let me tell you, it was a BLAST!🏂❄️ Fresh turns, stunning views, and the pure joy of being in the mountains... what more can I ask for?🤩 Swipe to see the action and don't forget to double tap if you're feeling the stoke! 🙌🏼 #splitboarding #powderday #arcticvalley #mountainsarecalling #neverstopexploring #backcountryskiing #winteradventure #snowboardinglife

Feeling like a kid again in the Alaskan backcountry 🌬️❄️🏔️ Splitboarding and catching some gnarly face shots in the powder snow! Nothing beats the thrill of carving through fresh snow in the wilderness 🙌 
Haha, I love Openchat AI! I no longer have to write descriptions. I just added some keywords and bam it does it for me 😂😎

#splitboarding #powderday #faceshots #alaska #backcountry #snowboarding #adventure #neverstopexploring 📷

Today was absolutely blower with @bigmountain_jo @nolan__253 @freshruin some of the best snow of the year so far! Not sure Japan's Japow can compete but definitely can't wait to find out next January 🗻

🏔️ Splitting the peaks in Hatcher Pass, Alaska

Feeling alive as I conquer the big mountains of Hatcher Pass on my splitboard 🔥 The endless powder fields and breathtaking views make for the ultimate snowboarding experience 🙌

#Splitboarding #Alaska #HatcherPass #Snowboarding #BackcountrySnowboarding #PowderDays #NatureLovers #AdventureSeeker #NeverStopExploring

🎿 Fresh powder, first tracks, and the thrill of skiing big mountains in Alaska 🏔️

Watch as @travismcadamz takes on the slopes with pure excitement and joy, leaving his mark on the freshly untouched powder. Breaking through the silence with the sound of his skis carving through the snow, this is what skiing is all about.

Take a break from the storms and join us for this unforgettable moment as Travis skis first tracks on the slopes of Alaska. Get ready to feel the rush of adrenaline and the pure bliss of skiing in the heart of the wilderness.

#Skiing #FirstTracks #FreshPowder #BigMountains #Alaska #NatureLovers #WinterWonderland #dji #djimini3

☀️ Soaking up the sun and the views on this splitboarding adventure in Alaska 🏔️

Taking in the stunning surroundings as we explore the big mountains of Alaska on our splitboards. Every turn brings a new breathtaking view, making this trip truly unforgettable.

Splitboarding in Alaska, with endless powder and majestic peaks, it will leave you in awe. The combination of the warm sun and the crisp mountain air makes for the perfect day on the slopes.

#Splitboarding #Alaska #BigMountains #NatureLovers #AdventureSeeker #PowderDays

✨ The Northern Lights - nature's very own fireworks display ✨

Watching the Aurora dance across the night sky is a truly unforgettable experience. It's a reminder of the magic and beauty of nature, and a moment that will stay with you forever.

Standing beneath the dazzling lights, we're reminded of just how small we are in this world. But in that moment, we're also filled with a sense of wonder and awe that makes us feel like anything is possible.

If you haven't seen the Northern Lights yet, it's an experience you won't want to miss. It's a display of nature's incredible power and beauty that leaves a lasting impression on all who witness it.

So come along with us and witness the magic of the Northern Lights. This is a moment you'll never forget.

#NorthernLights #Aurora #NatureLovers #StarryNight #AdventureSeeker #Travelgram #BucketList #NightSky #alaska

Top section of the S Couilor on Ptarmigan Peak in the front range of Alaska. Yesterday, myself @ginger_snowboy and Ben got into some dicey times in the front range. I was extra cautious on this top section. The conditions were cold -5f and windy, snow was well a bit dicey, especially the top section, which is a no fall zone above a cliff. Have to say we were all pretty pumped once we made it down and back to the snow machines 🙌

Blah blah blah.... Snowboarding
Write a caption...

It was such a nice day out. Got out there just after sunrise, and there was only 1 other person out. Got in 3 laps before everyone showed up. Some quality alone time just talking to myself and going my own pace. 
#snowboarding

Went on a big mission yesterday with @bigmountain_jo back in Turnagain. We started before sunrise in a complete whiteout and couldn't see more than a few feet in front of us. Eventually, the skies cleared, and we got some amazing views. Unfortunately, the conditions weren't right to right any big lines, but it was still a good time. 15 miles from sunrise to ridding the last section in the dark with headlamps. 
#dji #alaska #snowboarding

One of the coldest days out this year! When we left the car it said -7f. When it's that cold it makes everything more difficult. When I was trying to hand launch my drone from this spot it hit my finger and fell into the snow 🙄 luckily it fell right next to me and I was able to just pick it up but wasn't able to fly it after that. 
Really liking this new board from @wndr_alpine that @nick_russelll designed and stocked to be a FOW(friends of wonder) and work with such a cool company. 
#treadlightchargehard #wndralpine #snowboarding #splitboarding #freeride #powderday #steeplines #alaska

Japan hasn't disappointed! 
Today was the first day with clearish skys since I've been here, and we were finally able to get to the top of the mountain. 
#japan #jpow #powder #PowderDay #snowboarding #SnowboardDreams #treeskiing

Japan has been a wild ride. 
Got some blue skys on my first run on the backside of Niseko United today. On my second run the wind unfortunately kicked up and the clouds blew in, making it a complete white out.
I stupidity left my poles on the peak, so it looks like I'll be having to buy a new pair tomorrow. 
#japan #jpow #niseko #nisekojapan #snowboarding #powder #backcountry
